mongo-c-driver
------------------------------------------
The MongoDB C Driver, also known as “libmongoc”, is a library for using MongoDB
from C applications, and for writing MongoDB drivers in higher-level languages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.3-1
  cygwin-devel-3.6.3-1
  libbson2-devel-2.0.2-1bl1
  libbson2_2-2.0.2-1bl1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libmongoc2-devel-2.0.2-1bl1
  libmongoc2_2-2.0.2-1bl1
  libsasl2_3-2.1.27-1
  libsnappy1-1.2.2-1
  libssl3-3.0.16-2
  libutf8proc3-2.10.0-1bl1
  libzstd1-1.5.7-1
  pkg-config-2.4.3-1
  zlib0-1.3.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.44-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libsasl2-devel-2.1.27-1
  libsnappy-devel-1.2.2-1
  libssl-devel-3.0.16-2
  libutf8proc-devel-2.10.0-1bl1
  libzstd-devel-1.5.7-1
  ninja-1.12.1-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/archive/refs/tags/2.0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mongo-c-driver-2.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mongo-c-driver-2.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mongo-c-driver-2.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mongo-c-driver-2.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmongoc2_2-2.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmongoc2-devel-2.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbson2_2-2.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbson2-devel-2.0.2-X.tar.xz

